  <p class="lead">This page provides a summary of the system of Civil Registration (of births, marriages and deaths) in England and Wales and the General Register Office (GRO), a government office founded for this purpose. It, creates and holds centralised indexes of Births, Marriages and Deaths for England and Wales and has done so since July 1837. It is reliant on local Registrars, employed for nearly a century by the local Poor Law Commissioners and after 1929 by local government; as well as the local clergy and Registrars conducting marriages ceremonies.</p>  

