  <h2 id="changes"> Changes</h2>
 <h3>Registration Districts</h3>
  <h2> Holding area for stray items without a place </h2>
  <h3> Poor Law Counties / Union Counties </h3>
  <p> Peter Higginbotham [add reference] states, that for compiling statistics and for administration purposes, from 1834 Poor Law Unions were allocated to Poor Law Counties and that these were not always identical with the geographical counties. For instance, the allocated Poor Law County was often the county in which the main Poor town or district was located, but the Union included places in another county or counties. He also states that in 1850, prior to the 1851 census a few Unions had their allocated county changed. </p>
  <h3> Registration Districts </h3>
  <p> For further information [see our page: Registration Districts] [link to: Registration Districts] </p>
 <p> As discussed above, Registrations Districts were sub-districts of Poor Law Unions created under the Poor Law; and the General Registry Office when it indexed them sorted them into Volumes.</p>

